/td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   A variety of options</span><hr size=1> I've gotten wanderlust at lvl 30-31 so I thought I'd post all the options I've seen.<br>
<br>
1) Twilight Sea.  unfocused fire.  decent loot mostly dark blue spawns.  not bad, but exp slows some at 30, and quite a bit at 31.<br>
<br>
2) Najena.  I was able to run the 2 darkbones behind the fake wall, the magician room (until Trazdon spawned and ran me off), the gate magician, the single behind the gate magician, the crystal room, and the 2 darkbones in the prison (as well as assorted elementals) ina solo run.  Any of the magicians (goblin, named, or DE) as well as the darkbone skele's might drop focus items or mastery pages.  I was running 10 (8 after trazdon) spawns, and there are upwards of 14 not counting the goblins possible. The goblins seem to trade places with warriors so they aren't quite a reliable to run, and a swarm of green cons will take you down quickly. get help to try everything. =)  No real exp, but a good time to go get those focus items.  Took me 6 to 7 hours to get all 4, but its all up to luck here....<br>
<br>
** All of the below implies a focused fire pet, dual wielding, with summoned chain armor.  All of the above was unfocused fire, etc. etc.<br>
<br>
3) Dawnshroud peaks. I killed 3 shrooms, by NL zone, then got ran off by a wolf.  I hear the SS zone is a better place to start, but haven't been back since.  Didn't get any loot, but didn't stay long enough to find out what was possible.<br>
<br>
4) Marus Seru.  I grouped here just to check things out.  lvl 31 is too high to be here, everything is dark or light blue.  the mobs were many, but very socials, so adds should be expected.  Loot was almost non-existant.<br>
<br>
5) FM.  I solo'd 12 or so mountain giants out of the fort (blue and white cons).  pull with weak nuke, and heal fire pet to avoid aggro concerns.  Loot was exceptional (leg chopper, tree flayer, and grub digger all dropped for me), but exp wasn't anything to write home about.  Adds would pretty much have wiped me.<br>
<br>
6) EW and Rathe Mtns (NOT SOLO).  Paired up with a necro (lvl 35) and fought Ulthorks and Walruses in EW, and hill giants in Rathe.  Exp wasn't great in either and these wouldn't be good solo places until higher lvl (maybe 34, maybe not til 39).  Hill giant loot is good, but overcamped.  Necro was collecting ulthork tusks for a quest (and they seemed to be rare).  We spent as much time chatting as playing, this was just for fun...<br>
<br>
7) Golra's.  enough has been said about these already.  Solid exp, weak to avg loot. easy kills.  using lvl 1 nuke and pet heals you can keep 5-6 spawns down with some time for regen.  If you are better than me maybe you can run all the spawns (8 or 9).  boring. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
8 )  ... Wherever the mood takes me.  up for new suggestions as they come.<br>
<br>
Note: I did needilites at lvl 24 so I didn't go back at 29.  Now that you just have to do damage (and don't need to outdamage pet) the downtime is significant.  the exp is still good, and the fights are easy, but it gets too boring for words. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :x --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
<br>
