<br>
I haven't done a lot of validation, but based on &quot;feel&quot; it seems that healing a fire elemental is more mana efficient per kill than nuking things down in most situations.  Also I like being able to sit and med mid-fight.<br>
<br>
I don't avoid the nukes, but I save them for special situations (emergencies).  If I hadn't locked down my specialization at lvl 20 I think it would have gone abjuration... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Nuke the runners at low health, and nuke in serious situations, but most of the time I'm just helaer and buffer for my pet.<br>
<br>
And finally, the weakest heal seems the most mana efficient.  I get 8% of my fire pet's health for 25m, or 25% for 100m.  I hope this changes at some point, but even at lvl 34 I'm still using renew elements if I can get away with it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=fenobleu>Fenobleu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(9/13/02 7:54:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=44.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Renew Efficiency</span><hr size=1> According to lucy:<br>
<br>
By level 25 Renew Elements heals for 50pts.  It costs 25 mana to cast and thereby has a 2:1 ratio at and beyond level 25.<br>
<br>
Renew Summoning, however, costs 100 mana and initially heals for 120 (at level 20) and finally heals up to 220 (at level 60).  Renew Summoning does not achieve a 2:1 ratio until level 50.<br>
<br>
Conclusion:  Up until level 50 Renew Elements is more mana efficient than Renew Summoning.<br>
<br>
P.S.<br>
My only point on the weak nuke issue was that you may want to consider buying a white ceramic band so getting Burst of Flame takes up neither a slot nor mana.<br>
<br>
